17:09:56","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":9,"author":{"gitId":"Dylan-Liew"},"content":"","lastModifiedDate":"2026-02-26T17:09:56","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":10,"author":{"gitId":"Dylan-Liew"},"content":"Given below are my contributions to the project.","lastModifiedDate":"2026-02-26T17:09:56","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":11,"author":{"gitId":"Dylan-Liew"},"content":"","lastModifiedDate":"2026-02-26T17:09:56","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":12,"author":{"gitId":"Dylan-Liew"},"content":"* **New Feature**: Added the ability to undo/redo previous commands.","lastModifiedDate":"2026-02-26T17:09:56","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":13,"author":{"gitId":"Dylan-Liew"},"content":"  * What it does: allows the user to undo all previous commands one at a time. Preceding undo commands can be reversed by using the redo command.","lastModifiedDate":"2026-02-26T17:09:56","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":14,"author":{"gitId":"Dylan-Liew"},"content":"  * Justification: This feature improves the product significantly because a user can make mistakes in commands and the app should provide a convenient way to rectify them.","lastModifiedDate":"2026-02-26T17:09:56","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":15,"author":{"gitId":"Dylan-Liew"},"content":"  * Highlights: This enhancement affects existing commands and commands to be added in future. It required an in-depth analysis of design alternatives. The implementation too was challenging as it required changes to existing commands.","lastModifiedDate":"2026-02-26T17:09:56","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":16,"author":{"gitId":"Dylan-Liew"},"content":"  * Credits: *{mention here if you reused any code/ideas from elsewhere or if a third-party library is heavily used in the feature so that a reader can make a more accurate judgement of how much effort went into the feature}*","lastModifiedDate":"2026-02-26T17:09:56","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":17,"author":{"gitId":"Dylan-Liew"},"content":"","lastModifiedD